Rice straw liquefaction by sulfonated graphene oxide catalysts. The supercritical liquefaction of rice straw takes place at 320 °C, with 6.0 molar sulfuric acid and 10 weight % catalyst producing biofuel and biomass, with increasing the temperature. The syngas and biochar are produced from the catalytic conversion of rice straw. The increasing sulfuric acid concentration increases the syngas and biochar yields from rice straw
